    "description": "\nWinter weather travel advisory continues overnight.\n\nWhat:\nTotal snowfall amounts of 10 to 15 cm. Higher local amounts are possible.\nReduced visibility in areas of heavier snow.\n\nWhen:\nContinuing through overnight.\n\nAdditional information:\nSnow will taper off from west to east early this morning. It is possible that some areas will receive in excess of 15 cm.\n\n###\n\nMotorists should expect hazardous winter driving conditions and adjust travel plans accordingly.\n\nFor road conditions and other traveller information from the Ministry of Transportation, visit https://www.ontario.ca/511, https://www.twitter.com/511Ontario, or call 5-1-1.\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
    "instruction": "\nPrepare for quickly changing and deteriorating travel conditions. If visibility is reduced while driving, slow down, watch for tail lights ahead and be prepared to stop.\n",
